<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2013-12-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Chapter 495 Arterivirus Papain-like Proteinase 1α</TITLE><BODY>The third edition of the Handbook of Proteolytic Enzymes aims to be a comprehensive reference work for the enzymes that cleave proteins and peptides, and contains over 800 chapters. Each chapter is organized into sections describing the name and history, activity and specificity, structural chemistry, preparation, biological aspects, and distinguishing features for a specific peptidase. The subject of Chapter 498 is Arterivirus Papain-like Cysteine Proteinase α. Keywords: Arterivirus, autoproteolytic proteinase release, cytoplasm-to-nucleus transport, innate immunity control, multidomain proteinase, multifunctional proteinase, papain-like fold, polyprotein processing, RNA virus, single-cleavage proteinase, transcriptional control, virion formation control, zinc finger.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>